# modman manifest (Mibizum_Sync (Magento 1.x / OpenMage module))
#
# Maps the module files (left column, relative to THIS directory
# the module files) to their destination at the Magento root (right
# column). modman creates SYMLINKS, so editing the repo code is reflected in the
# store without redeploying (ideal for development).
#
# Recommended usage in this monorepo (local link, not clone):
#
#   cd /path/to/your/magento
#   modman init                                   # creates .modman/ (once)
#   modman link /path/to/magento-openMage
#   rm -rf var/cache/*                            # or Admin > Cache > Flush
#
# To update after a git pull of the repo: the symlinks already point to the new
# code; just flush the cache. `modman repair` recreates symlinks if something broke.
#
# NOTE on `modman clone <git-url>`: it clones the whole repo and looks for a
# `modman` file at the REPO ROOT. Since the module lives in a subdirectory of the
# monorepo here, `clone` does not fit directly; use `modman link` pointing to this
# directory, or deploy with composer / the packager .tgz.

# Module activator
src/app/etc/modules/Mibizum_Sync.xml                              app/etc/modules/Mibizum_Sync.xml

# Module code (community codePool)
src/app/code/community/Mibizum/Sync                               app/code/community/Mibizum/Sync

# Frontend layout + templates
src/app/design/frontend/base/default/layout/mibizum_sync.xml      app/design/frontend/base/default/layout/mibizum_sync.xml
src/app/design/frontend/base/default/template/mibizum_sync        app/design/frontend/base/default/template/mibizum_sync

# Admin layout + templates
src/app/design/adminhtml/default/default/layout/mibizum_sync.xml  app/design/adminhtml/default/default/layout/mibizum_sync.xml
src/app/design/adminhtml/default/default/template/mibizum_sync    app/design/adminhtml/default/default/template/mibizum_sync

